(LMDB Storage Overview) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Status: Alpha documentation snapshot \(2026-03-12\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This describes how Atho uses LMDB for chain, UTXO, mempool, orphan handling, and state) Tj
T*
(checkpoints. Paths and knobs are driven by Constants \(see Src/Utility/const.py\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Database layout and paths) Tj
T*
(- Root: blockchain_storage/<NETWORK_FOLDER>/ \(network-specific\).) Tj
T*
(- Main environments \(Constants.DATABASES\):) Tj
T*
(- full_block_chain.lmdb ? BlockStore \(blocks by height/hash\).) Tj
T*
(- utxo.lmdb ? UTXOStore.) Tj
T*
(- mempool.lmdb ? MempoolStore.) Tj
T*
(- orphan_blocks.lmdb ? orphan/side-branch staging \(OrphanReorgManager\).) Tj
T*
(- Additional LMDB:) Tj
T*
(- blockchain_storage/BlockData/state_hashes.lmdb ? StateTracker Merkle accumulator.) Tj
T*
(- Map sizes/bounds:) Tj
T*
(- Initial sizes: BLOCKSTORE_MAP_SIZE, UTXO_MAP_SIZE, MEMPOOL_MAP_SIZE, STATE_MAP_SIZE,) Tj
T*
(ORPHAN_MAP_SIZE.) Tj
T*
(- Per-store rollover ceilings: BLOCKSTORE_MAX_MAP_SIZE, UTXO_MAX_MAP_SIZE, MEMPOOL_MAX_MAP_SIZE,) Tj
T*
(STATE_MAX_MAP_SIZE, ORPHAN_MAX_MAP_SIZE.) Tj
T*
(- Global controls: LMDB_MAX_READERS, AUTO_RESIZE_LMDB, LMDB_GROWTH_FACTOR,) Tj
T*
(LMDB_MIN_GROWTH_STEP_BYTES, LMDB_ROLLOVER_ALERT_THRESHOLD, LMDB_RESIZE_RETRY_ATTEMPTS.) Tj
T*
(- Runtime logging: LMDB_STATUS_LOG_INTERVAL_SECONDS rate-limits memory-pressure logs while a) Tj
T*
(store is near its rollover threshold.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Rollover model) Tj
T*
(- Atho does not shard a single logical store across multiple LMDB environments yet.) Tj
T*
(- In current code, "rollover" means bounded LMDB map growth: when a write hits) Tj
T*
(lmdb.MapFullError, the store asks Src/Storage/lmdbutils.py for the next map size and grows the) Tj
T*
(existing environment.) Tj
T*
(- Growth is store-specific and stops at that store's configured *_MAX_MAP_SIZE.) Tj
T*
(- Once a store reaches its max map size, writes stop auto-growing and the node logs) Tj
T*
(lmdb_map_limit_reached. At that point you must raise the configured ceiling or archive/prune) Tj
T*
(data.) Tj
T*
(- While a store is near the rollover threshold, the node emits lmdb_memory_status log entries) Tj
T*
(with used_bytes, free_bytes, utilization_percent, and the next planned map size.) Tj
T*
(- Those LMDB memory events are also written to logs/<network>/storage/lmdb_memory.log so storage) Tj
T*
(pressure is preserved even if terminal log filtering is enabled.) Tj
T*
(- Stores expose lmdb_status\(\) and the aggregate checker in Src/Storage/dbcheck.py reports) Tj
T*
(used_bytes, free_bytes, utilization_percent, near_rollover, and next_map_size.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(BlockStore \(Src/Storage/blockstorage.py\)) Tj
T*
(- Keys:) Tj
T*
(- blk:h:<height> ? compact JSON block.) Tj
T*
(- blk:x:<hash> ? compact JSON block.) Tj
T*
(- blk:t:<txid> ? tx location index payload \(block_height, block_hash, tx_index\).) Tj
T*
(- meta:blk:txindex_ready ? tx-index readiness marker.) Tj
T*
(- Serialization: to_compact/from_compact\("Block", ...\); Decimal/bytes serialized via custom JSON) Tj
T*
(hook.) Tj
T*
(- Writes: put_block enforces network, normalizes index/height, merges witness info, prunes) Tj
T*
(witnesses for old blocks based on retention, and writes both height/hash keys in one LMDB txn.) Tj
T*
ET
endstream
endobj
