(- Internal write helpers retry on MapFullError and grow the mempool map within its configured) Tj
T*
(ceiling.) Tj
T*
(- Consensus writes: use mempool.consensus_write_context when invoked from) Tj
T*
(ConsensusSupervisor.accept_tx/accept_block.) Tj
T*
(- Diagnostics: lmdb_status\(\) reports utilization and rollover readiness.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Orphan/side-branch storage \(Src/Blockchain/orphreorgs.py\)) Tj
T*
(- Environment: blockchain_storage/BlockData/orphan.lmdb \(network-specific via) Tj
T*
(Constants.DATABASES["orphan_blocks"] when set\).) Tj
T*
(- Stores orphan/side-branch blocks for later reorg consideration. Orphan writes retry with the) Tj
T*
(shared rollover helper and stop at ORPHAN_MAX_MAP_SIZE.) Tj
T*
(- Reorg application rewinds/applies UTXO using stored branches.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(State checkpoint LMDB \(Src/Main/state.py\)) Tj
T*
(- Environment: blockchain_storage/BlockData/state_hashes.lmdb.) Tj
T*
(- Stores leaves leaf:<height> with payload {height, block_hash, leaf, state_root, chain_hash,) Tj
T*
(status}. State root is a Merkle accumulator over \(height:block_hash\) leaves \(SHA3-384\).) Tj
T*
(- State leaf writes retry with the shared rollover helper. Auto-growth is controlled by) Tj
T*
(STATE_LMDB_GROWTH_FACTOR and capped by STATE_MAX_MAP_SIZE.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Non-LMDB telemetry persistence \(network hashrate\)) Tj
T*
(- Network hashrate aggregation is intentionally file-based JSON/JSONL \(not LMDB\):) Tj
T*
(- logs/<network>/network/network_hashrate_live.json) Tj
T*
(- logs/<network>/network/network_hashrate_state.json) Tj
T*
(- logs/<network>/network/network_hashrate_history.jsonl) Tj
T*
(- This data powers /network/hashrate* API responses and chart windows.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Concurrency and safety) Tj
T*
(- LMDB readers are many; writers are single per environment. Code opens envs with max_readers) Tj
T*
(from Constants.) Tj
T*
(- Consensus guards \(consensus_write_context\) prevent accidental writes when) Tj
T*
(ENFORCE_CONSENSUS_WRITE is enabled.) Tj
T*
(- Write operations catch lmdb.MapFullError and optionally roll the map up to the next configured) Tj
T*
(size; if AUTO_RESIZE_LMDB is off or the store is already at its ceiling, callers must enlarge) Tj
T*
(the configured map size manually.) Tj
T*
(- Pruning: witness data can be pruned in persisted blocks based on retention \(WITNESS_*) Tj
T*
(constants\); reads may return pruned witness maps for old heights.) Tj
T*
(- Important LMDB behavior: pruning frees pages for reuse by future writes, but it does not) Tj
T*
(shrink the already-allocated map_size. If you want a smaller file footprint after heavy pruning,) Tj
T*
(you need an explicit LMDB compaction/export step.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Operational tips) Tj
T*
(- Use python3 Src/Storage/dbcheck.py to inspect all LMDB stores and see how close each one is to) Tj
T*
(rollover.) Tj
T*
(- If a store reports near_rollover, raise that store's *_MAX_MAP_SIZE before it reaches the) Tj
T*
(ceiling.) Tj
T*
(- If you hit MapFullError, check whether the store already reached its *_MAX_MAP_SIZE; if so,) Tj
T*
(raise the limit or prune/archive data before retrying.) Tj
T*
(- Backups: stop writers, copy the LMDB directory \(env is a few files\). Avoid copying while) Tj
T*
(writes are in flight unless you use LMDB?s copy\(\) API \(not wrapped here\).) Tj
T*
(- Permissions: ensure blockchain_storage/... is writable by the node user; map sizes allocate) Tj
T*
(virtual space, not immediate disk, but plan for growth.) Tj
T*
ET
endstream
